.SH NAME
SpeechRecognition.start_event \- SpeechRecognition: start event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]start\f[B]\f[R] event of the Web Speech API
\f[CR]SpeechRecognition\f[R] object is fired when the speech recognition
service has begun listening to incoming audio with intent to recognize
grammars associated with the current \f[CR]SpeechRecognition\f[R].
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\(dqstart\(dq, (event) => { })

onstart = (event) => { }
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A generic \f[CR]Event\f[R] with no added properties.
.SH EXAMPLES
You can use the \f[CR]start\f[R] event in an \f[CR]addEventListener\f[R]
method:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] recognition = \f[B]new\f[R] webkitSpeechRecognition() || \f[B]new\f[R] SpeechRecognition();

recognition.addEventListener(\(dqstart\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  console.log(\(dqSpeech recognition service has started\(dq);
});
.EE
.PP
Or use the \f[CR]onstart\f[R] event handler property:
.IP
.EX
recognition.onstart = () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  console.log(\(dqSpeech recognition service has started\(dq);
};
.EE
